---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
---

<Article
  title="Longest Road Rules in Catan: When Does It Switch?"
  description="The complete guide to Longest Road — how to earn it, lose it, and the edge cases that cause arguments."
  game="catan"
  gameTitle="Catan"
  category="Rules"
  product="catan-score-tracker"
  publishDate="2025-05-06"
>
  <p>
    The Longest Road card is worth 2 victory points and causes more arguments
    than any other rule in Catan. When does it switch? Can settlements break a
    road? What happens in a tie?
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="You need at least 5 consecutive road segments to claim Longest Road. If someone builds a longer continuous road, they take it. If yours gets broken by an opponent's settlement, recalculate." />

  <h2>The Basic Rules</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-3">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">✅</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-emerald-800">Minimum 5 segments</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-emerald-700/70 mt-1">You need at least 5 consecutive road pieces to claim the Longest Road card.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">✅</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-emerald-800">Must be continuous</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-emerald-700/70 mt-1">The road must be an unbroken chain. Branches count — you use the longest single path through your road network.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">✅</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-emerald-800">Your settlements don't break it</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-emerald-700/70 mt-1">Your own settlements and cities along the road do NOT break your chain — the road continues through them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>When Does Longest Road Switch?</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-4">
    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-blue-400">
      <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-bark mb-2">Scenario 1: Someone Builds a Longer Road</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        If another player builds a continuous road that's longer than yours, they
        immediately take the Longest Road card. They must <strong>exceed</strong> your
        length — tying is not enough.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-red-400">
      <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-bark mb-2">Scenario 2: Your Road Gets Broken</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        An opponent builds a settlement at an intersection along your road, breaking
        your chain. Recalculate the longest continuous segment of your remaining road.
        If it's no longer the longest, the card moves — or goes back to the supply if
        no one has 5+.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400">
      <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-bark mb-2">Scenario 3: Tie After a Break</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        If your road gets broken and the remaining segment ties with another player who
        already had a long road, <strong>nobody gets the card</strong>. It returns to the
        supply until someone has a clear longest road of 5+.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="rule" title="The Tie Rule">
    You must <strong>strictly exceed</strong> the current longest road to take the card. If you tie, the current holder keeps it. If the holder loses it due to a break and multiple players are tied, nobody gets it.
  </InfoBox>

  <h2>Edge Cases That Cause Arguments</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-3">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">❓</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">"Can an opponent's settlement break my road?"</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-700/70 mt-1"><strong>Yes.</strong> If another player builds a settlement at an intersection along your road, it splits your road into two separate chains.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">❓</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">"Does a loop/circle count?"</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-700/70 mt-1"><strong>Yes</strong>, loops are valid road segments. Count the longest path through the loop (don't double-count any segment).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <span class="text-lg shrink-0">❓</span>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-blue-800">"Do ships count in Seafarers?"</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-blue-700/70 mt-1"><strong>Yes.</strong> Ships and roads both count as segments for Longest Road (called "Longest Trade Route" in Seafarers).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="Strategic Tip: Road Blocking">
    Building a settlement on someone's road is one of the most aggressive moves in Catan. It costs you a settlement (limited to 5), but it can steal 2 VP from the leader. Use this when someone is racing to 10 points.
  </InfoBox>
</Article>
